article.headline: Wichita State 78, Bradley 57
article.story: WICHITA, Kan. (AP) -- Sophomore Paul Miller scored a career best 22 points and grabbed 10 rebounds as Wichita State led from start to finish to defeat Bradley 78-57 in a Missouri Valley Conference game Sunday. Wichita State (15-7, 8-4) bolted to a 40-20 lead at halftime and stretched its lead to 57-24 with 13:29 left in the game after Aaron Hogg scored inside. Miller, who averaged only. 7.9 points a game, got 14 of his points in the second half. He scored a couple baskets from close range and hit a free throw to highlight a 10-0 run that got the Shockers the game-high 33-point spread. Bradley (10-13, 3-9) could never get much of anything going the entire game, getting no closer than 19 points the rest of the way. Phillip Gilbert, the Braves' leading scorer with a 17.8 point average, finished the game with only eight points. He did not score in the second half. Marcellus Sommerville, a 16.1 point scorer, got only 11 points, two in the second half, and James Gillingham, a 15.9 point scorer, had only five points. The only other Bradley player in double figures was reserve Jabbar Battle, with 10 points. He hit 4-of-4 goals but the team shot only 34.4 percent. In addition to Miller, Jamar Howard and Hogg were in double-figure scoring with 13 points each.
